[start section id="20112"]

#1 Sigmoid adenocarcinoma, grade 3 of 4, pT3, N0, M0, status-post sigmoid resection and multiple (16) lymph node dissection with negative surgical margins
At this time, there are no clear high-risk features other than a moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma and a T3 lesion.  The surgical margins are negative.  There is no evidence of nodal involvement and multiple (16) lymph nodes were included in the specimen and all were negative for malignancy.  Based on these findings and multiple comorbid conditions, we discussed about the controversial role of chemotherapy in this setting.  Clearly, he does not appear to be a candidate for any adjuvant chemotherapy based on his tumor characteristics and overall medical conditions.  He would require periodic followup with three-monthly checkup of CEA levels, and his next CT-scan should be performed in six-months.  He should undergo colonoscopy one-year from the diagnosis of his colon cancer (January 2011).  I would ask him to continue on iron pills.  Clearly, there is evidence of iron-deficiency anemia, but there is an improvement in his hemoglobin.
I suggested that he be evaluated by our cardiologists for possible anticoagulation and optimization of his cardiac medications due to severe ischemic cardiomyopathy along with atrial fibrillation.  At this time, he does not wish to be on Coumadin, and he understands the risks including that of stroke if he is not on chronic anticoagulation.  He does not wish to follow-up with cardiologists for now.  He has multiple medical issues including diabetic neuropathy for which he is currently receiving Neurontin and has been following-up with a diabetologist closer to home.  At this point, I would not get a KRAS testing done; however, in the future if there is a need, we could always get it.  Currently, we are not recommending any form of adjuvant therapy.  I indicated that his siblings/children/first-degree relatives should undergo colonoscopic evaluation at the age of 50.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

[end section id="20112"]

