[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Robinson is a very pleasant 72-year-old gentleman with the following oncologic history.
1.  January 27, 2010 - First ever colonoscopy to the cecum performed due to anemia.  A mass was located 35 cm from the anal verge.  This was biopsy positive for moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma with evidence of invasion.
2.  February 23, 2010 - Underwent heart catheterization, do not have those reports.
3.  April 27, 2010 - Presented to Edgerton Womens Center New York Foundling Hospital for further evaluation.  CT abdomen and pelvis negative for colonic mass or liver metastasis.
4.  April 29, 2010 - Echocardiogram noting severe left ventricular enlargement with an ejection fraction at 26%.  Akinesis of the inferior, inferolateral and anterolateral walls of the left ventricle.  Trivial mitral valve regurg with severe left atrial enlargement.  Mildly enlarged right ventricle.  Mild tricuspid valve regurgitation and severe right atrial enlargement.
5.  May 12, 2010 - Dr. Otoole performed a sigmoid resection.  Per operative report, there was no evidence of any metastatic disease within the abdomen.  Pathology of the sigmoid tissue positive for invasive grade 3 (of 4) adenocarcinoma.  Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolonic fat.  Negative surgical margins.  (12) diverticular identified.  Of 16 regional lymph nodes removed, all were negative for malignancy (pT3, N0).
Today, he comes to discuss the adjuvant chemotherapy.  Notably, he has multiple medical comorbidities including severe CHF and coronary artery disease with several MIs in the past.  He denies any chest pain.  He states his shortness-of-breath is at its baseline.  He denies any recent unintentional weight-loss.  He denies nausea, vomiting.  He states that occasionally he gets constipated with iron pills, and at times with use of laxatives he gets loose bowel movements.  He denies any rectal bleeding.  He does state that his stools are black since initiation of iron.  He denies any bone pain or headache.  He denies any cough.

